      "writtenOn": "2020-06-19T15:26:03Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Maybe, but at the moment it\u0027s used in cpp code generation when the parent .fp uses sample(matrix) and sample(float2) on the same child. If this is detected at the sksl analysis level as a variable matrix, then functionally there\u0027s no difference to just registering the child with the variable matrix since those are marked as explicitly sampled. Then it\u0027s just a matter of preference for a shorter arg list, or emphasizing the two approaches used in the shader code",
