      "writtenOn": "2020-06-19T15:26:03Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "No, not temporary. All FPs currently have up to 1 coord transform, and 0 if they don\u0027t access local coords at all. sk_TransformedCoords2D is the only builtin that .fp files use to access the local coords and I didn\u0027t want to complicate things by updating it to use a better variable.\n\nIn the end, I do think we remove this and just have a built-in variable reference to sk_LocalCoord or similar for .fps.  In my next CL, this block is even further gutted to just point the \u0027%s\u0027 format arg to \u0027args.fLocalCoord\u0027. At that point, this could then be moved to a different builtin but would involve updating all the .fp files. I think that should be a later CL.",
